additional_info:
To change style, run:

(function(){
    var id = [1,2,3,4]; //modified the style id you want to change HERE!!
    var service = Components.classes["@userstyles.org/style;1"].getService(Components.interfaces.stylishStyle)
    for (var i=0; i < id.length; i++){
        var style = service.find(id[i], service.REGISTER_STYLE_ON_CHANGE); 
        style.enabled = !style.enabled;
        style.save();
    }
})();


the command can be run in keyconfig or fireguesture, also any other run in browser envirnment ( e.g. Scratchpad with "devtools.chrome.enabled" = true )

This CSS will make you style manager kind of ugly , I suggest that enable it only when needed:)
